---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>🚀 Visualizing Agentic Payments</h1>
			<p>
				Welcome to <strong>payarch.dev</strong>. We are building open-source tools and deep-dive technical explorations for designing agentic payment architectures. 
			</p>
			<p>
				Financial infrastructure is complex. When you introduce autonomous AI agents acting on behalf of users—negotiating, holding funds, and settling ledgers—it becomes even harder to visualize. We break down these flows step-by-step from business intent, to technical API calls, all the way down to ISO 8583.
			</p>
			<p>Check out our interactive diagrams:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="/blog/agentic-checkout-e2e">Agentic Checkout E2E: How an AI agent buys a $90 headphone</a></li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				Built with Astro, React Flow, and TailwindCSS. <br/>
				Explore the core schemas and source code on <a href="https://github.com/ivalenzuelan/payarch-blog">GitHub</a>.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
